Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal of Sokoto State has appointed an eight-man committee to deliberate on the harmonisation of the framework to be adopted for the autonomy of the legislature and judiciary as it affects the two arms of government in the state. The state committee, according to the governor will be chaired by his Deputy, Hon. Manir Muhammad Dan Iya. Other members include the Deputy Speaker, Rt. Hon. Abubakar Magaji, the state Attorney-General and Commissioner for Justice, Suleiman Usman (SAN) and the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Mallam Saidu Umar. Others include the state’s Head of Service, Alhaji Sani Garba Shuni, Clerk of the Sokoto State House of Assembly (SOHA), Mallam Abdul-Razaq Shehu, the Chief Registrars of the state’s High Court and Sharia Court, Barrister Bashir Ibrahim and Alhaji Idris Adamu respectively. ALSO READ: BBNaijaLockdown: 5 things you need to know about the rapper philosopher Laycon A statement by the special adviser on media and publicity to governor, Muhammad Bello, said Gov. Tambuwal, who is also the Vice-Chairman of the NGF, disclosed that the committee was set up without prejudice to the subsisting federal government arrangements on the matter. It will be recalled that last month, the governor noted that the question of autonomy for the legislature and judiciary “is only a question of working on the framework, because the Order 10 of Mr President came up with a framework for the Judiciary,” to the exclusion of all the state legislature. “And there were some states that were already having different frameworks. So, we need to harmonize and come up with a common framework that will work in the interest of these are institutions,” he stated. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE N1.32bn, not N1.5bn, was spent on COVID-19 palliatives, Pondei explains THE ongoing investigative hearing into the allegations bordering on misappropriation of N81.5 billion by the management of Niger Delta  Development Commis